When I read the question, I thought it was a little unclear. I am pretty sure you are asking for a way to send an email to everybody who has a given role and/or role group in a role hierarchy.

If this is the case, there is a built in, very useful function in Exchange that you can use.

Go to your Exchange Server, navigate to the Exchange Admin Center, and navigate to Roles --> Role Groups --> Select a Role Group.

After you select the Role Group, you will see a button that says "Send an E-Mail". Click it.

There you will be able to type and send an email to everyone in that role group.

Answer: You can do it by creating a role group and assign the desired users to it.

Then create a custom mail template and set the recipient of the custom mail template to the role group. You can create a custom mail template by going to the EAC and then Mail Flow -> Mail Template.

Then you can create a rule and attach the custom mail template to it.

The rule can be created in EAC -> Mail Flow -> Rules.

You can create a rule that whenever a new user is created in AD, the user will receive a welcome email by attaching the custom mail template and the recipient of the custom mail template will be the role group you have assigned to the new users.

