I'd say that if you're looking for ideas, that's the place to be.

\strong{The most important thing is to look at what is happening in the real world.}

Are there any technologies that are close to the point where they will make a huge impact on society? For instance, self-driving cars. It's not here now, but it could be soon.

Are there any technologies that have the potential to make the biggest impact on society? For instance, genetic engineering. It's not here now, but it could be soon.

Are there any technologies that are already making a huge impact on society? For instance, smartphones.

\strong{Also, I'd recommend that you don't think of one technology changing society.}

Instead, think of society changing because of many technologies, each one making a small impact.

For instance, genetic engineering, self-driving cars, and smartphones could all come together to change society.
\begin{itemize}
\item People can live where they want. They don't have to worry about getting to work
\item People don't have to worry about pollution from transportation.
\item People can spend more time doing the things they want to do.
\end{itemize}

\strong{I'd also recommend that you don't think of one technology changing society for the better or worse.}

Instead, think of society changing because of many technologies, each one making a small impact.

For instance, genetic engineering, self-driving cars, and smartphones could all come together to change society.
\begin{itemize}
\item People can live where they want. They don't have to worry about getting to work.
\item People can use genetic engineering to choose the healthiest lifestyle.
\item People can spend more time doing the things they want to do.
\item People can't drive, so they spend more time online.
\item People have to use genetic engineering to stay healthy.
\end{itemize}

\strong{I'd also recommend that you focus on the social impact of the technology, rather than the technology itself.}

For instance, I could say that smartphones have made society worse by:
\begin{itemize}
\item Making people less social
\item Making people less healthy
\item Making people less productive
\end{itemize}

Or I could say that smartphones have made society better by:
\begin{itemize}
\item Making people less bored
\item Making it easier to meet new people
\item Making it easier to do research
\end{itemize}

So my recommendation is that you use the technology to change society. Then change society to make it more interesting.

