I'm feeling a bit lonely these days, how can I make new friends?
\end{blockquote}

A common way to meet new people is to join a club.  The thing about clubs is that you have to go to meetings, and you have to participate.  It can be hard to go to meetings at the same time each week, but that's the deal.  I would say clubs are best for people that are reasonably extroverted.

\begin{blockquote}

What are the most effective ways to meet people?
\end{blockquote}

Well, this is more of a social skill question, so I would say you should start by asking people you find interesting.  This can be hard, because people can be shy, but if you are comfortable asking questions that's a good start.  You can also try joining an activity or a club.  Some clubs are more social than others.  If you want to try to meet some people that are like-minded, you can try looking for a club based on the kind of things you like to do.

\begin{blockquote}

I've tried a lot of clubs and activities, but I'm not making any friends.
\end{blockquote}

Well, that's not great.  First, what kinds of clubs and activities have you tried?  Have you tried any that are more social?  You can always try something social that you think you might like.  Maybe you could try joining a sports team, or a group that does something active.  You could also try meeting people in person by joining a group that meets to do something you like.  You could try something like a board gaming club, or a writing club, or a club that does a hobby you like.

\begin{blockquote}

I'm not very good at making small talk.
\end{blockquote}

Well, I think this is a bit of a common problem, and I think it's kind of hard to get good at.  The thing is, small talk isn't really about small talk.  It's about getting to know someone, and finding things that you have in common.  I would say the best way to get good at small talk is to practice.  You can practice by talking to random people, but I think it's better to pick a few people that you might find interesting, and talk to them.  You can try to find something that you like in common, and ask questions about that.  It's all about finding a way to connect.  You can also try to practice by talking to people online.

