One of the key ethical considerations for using AI in healthcare is the potential for discrimination and bias. AI algorithms are trained on data sets, and if the data sets are not representative of the population or contain biased information, the algorithms may produce biased results. This could lead to unfair treatment of patients, particularly those from underrepresented groups.

