\begin{blockquote}

Specifically, we propose a multi-task learning framework to jointly train multiple tasks with multiple sub-networks, where each task is assigned to a different sub-network. We show that the multi-task learning framework can be naturally extended to multi-task learning with partial training data, which is critical for many real-world applications. Our experiments show that the proposed multi-task learning framework outperforms existing single-task learning methods on a variety of natural language processing tasks, even when the training data is incomplete.
