I don't think there is any clear cut answer to this question. I have worked at both environments and here's my take:

\strong{Strengths of a Startup:}
\begin{itemize}
\item There is a huge opportunity to learn and evolve through the process of working in a startup. Due to the fast paced nature of a startup, you are likely to be pushed in to learning new things and also to apply all your skills to make a difference.
\item More autonomy to do work. You can be more hands on and take up responsibilities. This is a very important point for me. I personally do not like to be told what to do but rather be given a task and allowed to come up with ways to achieve it.
\item You'll usually work directly with the core team. You don't have to go through the hierarchy to get your work done. This can be a double edged sword but I'll explain why in the next point.
\item You will be more visible. You may be part of the core team and your opinion will be more valued.
\end{itemize}

\strong{Weaknesses of a Startup:}
\begin{itemize}
\item You will have less resources to work with. You'll have to be more creative and resourceful to get your work done.
\item You will not have much of a support system. You'll have to work on your own more often.
\item You'll have to do more work than the big companies. The amount of work will be much higher.
\item You'll have to work more hours. Most startups will have you working late into the night.
\item The compensation might not be as good as the big tech giants.
\item You might be pulled in to other areas of the business where you're not skilled.
\end{itemize}

\strong{Strengths of a Tech Giant:}
\begin{itemize}
\item More money. You'll have more resources and more financial muscle to work with.
\item Better brand recognition. You'll get better opportunities to work with bigger clients, better pay for consulting work etc.
\item Better healthcare and other benefits.
\end{itemize}

\strong{Weaknesses of a Tech Giant:}
\begin{itemize}
\item More bureaucracy. As they are much larger companies, more decisions must be made. This can lead to a lot of red tape and slow decision making.
\item You will have a strict hierarchy. You'll have to go through the hierarchy to get your work done.
\item You'll have less visibility. You won't be part of the core team and your opinion will not be valued as much.
\item Less autonomy to do work. You'll have to follow orders and do things the way they want it to be done.
\end{itemize}

\strong{My Pick:} I would work in a startup. I've worked in both environments and I personally prefer working in a startup. I think there's more learning and more growth opportunities in a startup than a tech giant. However, I do believe that working in a tech giant has its own strengths.

