I could talk for hours about the ridiculous things that have gone on in my tenure as a software engineer.  I'll try to keep it succinct and give you a few, and then encourage you to ask for more.

\section{Cube Farm}

I used to work in cube farms, and there were always interesting stories.  I'll tell you a couple:

\section{The Dirty Dish}

There was this one guy who was a bit of a slob.  I mean, he was a bit of a slob in general, but in his cube in particular.  It was just a generally nasty place.  So one day I was sitting there watching him do some work, and he had a big bowl of cereal, and he left it in the bowl on his desk, sitting there right in the middle of all the other crap.  After a while, I noticed that the bowl wasn't empty, and he was still eating out of it.  Then I noticed the bowl was moving.  He had a mouse in there.  A mouse that must be starving, because it came out of the bowl and ate some cereal, then tried to get back in the bowl.  It couldn't.  It was too big.  So he picked up the bowl and shoved it back in.  The mouse was so hungry it came right back out, and tried to get back in the bowl again.  This went on for a while, and I was laughing so hard I was crying.  The guy never noticed.  He was a slob, but he didn't deserve that.

\section{The Paper Cup}

Another guy in the cube farm was a bit of a klutz, but there was one story that was kind of funny.  This was before the days of big cups of coffee.  Most people had little paper cups.  Anyway, this guy had a cup of coffee that he'd finished.  Or so he thought.  He went back to his desk and sat down, and all of a sudden he felt a warm wetness on his back.  He turned around, and the cup was empty.  Not only was it empty, but the bottom had been cut out.  He couldn't figure out how it happened, but it must have been a mouse, or something.  He got up to go to the bathroom to get another cup, and as he was walking to the bathroom, he saw the source of the leak.  It was the little mouse that had been living in his cube.  It had chewed a hole in the bottom of the cup.  I'm not sure how it managed to get into the cup, but I'm sure it was a bit of mischief, and the guy didn't appreciate it too much, but I got a good laugh out of it.

