\section{Find a Race Track}

\section{What it does}

Searches for a track name, city, and state and returns the corresponding track.

\section{How it works}

I use the [Google Maps API](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/maps/start) to return a google map of the area with the track highlighted. I then use [Google's place search](https://developers.google.com/places/documentation/search#PlaceSearchRequests) to find the track with the [Google Maps GeoCode API](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/geocoding).

\section{Live Demo}

[View the live demo here](http://www.google.com/fusiontables/DataSource?snapid=S56213_1qD2&docid=16C76u4nDqw25PtJ8dJGwIb2LsOY-ZdWj1yXLKx3) and [view the source code here](http://www.google.com/fusiontables/DataSource?snapid=S56213_1qD2&docid=16C76u4nDqw25PtJ8dJGwIb2LsOY-ZdWj1yXLKx3)

\section{Code Sample}

\begin{code}
