Encourage users to choose passwords that are:
\begin{itemize}
\item complex (for example, a passphrase)
\item random
\item private
\end{itemize}

\section{The explanation}

People choose to use passwords that are easy to remember because they don't want to have to change their password every 3-6 months.

So if you really want to improve security, you should not force users to change their passwords. Instead, you should try to encourage them to choose passwords that are as secure as possible.

