It sounds like you are not being laid off, but rather being forced out. This is not the same thing.

The company can't legally "push" you out the door. If you refuse to leave, they can only terminate you for cause.

There are many reasons why a company might want you to leave. For instance, if you are in a small company, and you have been performing poorly, your continued presence at work is a toxic influence.

The company can't legally deny you a severance package, but they can make it much smaller than you were expecting if they are going to pay you out. They can also make you sign an agreement to not sue them, or sign an agreement stating that they can't be sued for anything.

